==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rudimentary
<hw>Ru`di*men"ta*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>rudimentaire</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to
rudiments; consisting in first principles; elementary; initial; <as>as,
<ex>rudimental</ex> essays</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Very imperfectly developed; in an
early stage of development; embryonic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rudish</ent>⟦br⟧
